    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - TRANSFER CASES - ASSEMBLE - UPPER SHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="9">
        <title>UPPER SHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303459">Figure 59</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1303459" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303459.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 59. Upper Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place input gear into housing HUB UP
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303460">(Figure 60)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303460" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303460.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 60. Install Input Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put a light coat of lubrication on input seal lip and install into bearing cap
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303461">(Figure 61)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303461" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303461.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Lubricate Input Seal And Install</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn input bearing cap over and press in bearing
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303462">(Figure 62)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303462" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303462.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 62. Press in Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position new gasket on housing, aligning bolt holes
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303463">(Figure 63)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303463" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303463.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Install New Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble bearing cap to housing. Secure in place with twelve (12) bolts and lockwashers
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303464">(Figure 64)</hotlnk>. Tighten bolts 46 to 54 Nm (34 to 40 ft-lbs).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303464" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303464.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 64. Install Bearing Cap To Housing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>For convenience, the lower shaft bearing and a bearing cap can be installed at this time.
                        Refer to ASSEMBLE,
                        <hotlnk document="s13034_17.xml" xrefid="x1303402">LOWER SHAFT</hotlnk>
                        section.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press new bearing onto upper input shaft, and install snap ring into groove. Position spacer
                onto input shaft next to bearing, as shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303465">Figure 65.</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303465" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303465.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Position Spacer Onto Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn transfer case over and start input shaft splines into input gear
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303466">(Figure 66)</hotlnk>. Be certain input gear is aligned with opposite bearing,
                so damage to threads and shaft does not occur. Use a soft hammer to tap shaft through input gear until
                it bottoms out.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303466" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303466.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 66. Install Shaft Splines Into Input Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position new gasket onto the housing and install adapter plate. Secure with eight (8) socket
                head bolts and lockwashers. Tighten bolts to 47 to 54 Nm (35 to 45 ft-lbs).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install end yoke, companion flange or spacer onto shaft
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303467">(Figure 67)</hotlnk>. Secure with washer and new self-locking nut and tighten
                to 542 to 610 Nm (400 to 450 ft-lbs). Lubricate roller bearing and install in the end of input shaft.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303467" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303467.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 67. Install End Yoke, Companion Flange Or Spacer Onto Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
